Day 3 of breaking down @ZeusRWA’s RWA asset class guide. 

Today is Private Credit…

Onchain lending to businesses, real estate sponsors, and emerging market borrowers. The yield engine of RWAs.

Projects off the top of my head⬇️

@maplefinance - institutional onchain lending, $4B + deployed, Syrup retail product

@centrifuge - tokenized credit pools, longest-running infrastructure in the space

@pactfinance - $1.9B+ in tokenized private credit & RWAs, had them on @WALLY_DAO spaces yesterday so check that out!

@goldfinch_fi - uncollateralized lending to emerging market businesses

@clearpoolfin - institutional credit markets with permissionless pools

@humafinance Finance - receivables-backed lending and PayFi infrastructure

@paretocredit - composable private credit, integrated with Gauntlet + Morpho & also were on our X spaces yesterday

@ZivoeProtocol - RWA credit protocol, 13.80% APY base yield

@Textileprotocol - composable private credit, just went live Feb 2026

@saturn_credit - 11%+ yield backed by Bitcoin, incubated by YZi Labs

@MuDigitalHQ - stablecoin yields backed by Asia Credit, unlocking the $20T Asian credit market

Distributed value sits at $4.96B (-18.16% / 30d). The only RWA sector that contracted in April. No worries there, it will recover.

kept.text:
Securitize gets FINRA approval to expand into tokenized securities

@Securitize has received CMA approval from FINRA, becoming the first broker-dealer able to custody tokenized securities and offer full-stack onchain IPO infrastructure.

The approval enables atomic swaps and real-time settlement between tokenized assets and stablecoins, with transactions executed in a single step.

